# tm1637

Bit-banged driver for the **TM1637** 4-digit 7-segment LED display.

## Hardware connection

| TM1637 pin | ESP32-C3 GPIO |
| ---------- | ------------- |
| CLK        | GPIO 0        |
| DIO        | GPIO 1        |
| VCC        | 3.3 V         |
| GND        | GND           |

Both CLK and DIO lines are driven as **open-drain with internal pull-up**.

## API

```c
// Initialise the display. Must be called once before any other function.
void tm1637_init(int clk_gpio, int dio_gpio);

// Show time as HH:MM with colon between digits 1 and 2.
void tm1637_show_time(uint8_t h, uint8_t m);

// Show a 2-digit value right-aligned: [ - | - | d0 | d1 ]
void tm1637_show_right(uint8_t val);

// Show a 2-digit value left-aligned:  [ d0 | d1 | - | - ]
void tm1637_show_left(uint8_t val);

// Send 4 raw segment bytes.  seg[1] bit 7 controls the colon.
void tm1637_send_raw(uint8_t seg[4]);
```

## Protocol notes

Communication follows the TM1637 two-wire protocol:
1. Start condition — DIO falls while CLK is high.
2. Bytes transmitted LSB-first; each bit is clocked on the rising edge of CLK.
3. After each byte the master releases DIO and the device pulls it low as ACK.
4. Stop condition — DIO rises while CLK is high.
